g.data-name: Backing infrastructure is implementation-specific i.e. it may be containers serverless VMs etc.
New feature bug fix is designed and ticketed
Development Team member selects a ticket and creates a git topic branch to begin work
When ready for review the Development Team member opens a merge request
The merge request initiates a series of automations that results in a new preview
Reviewer Approver tests the feature and provides feedback directly to the Developer.
The Developer commits the relevant changes which are automatically updated at the preview URL.
The preview is available at a shareable secure URL
The iterative cycle between the Developer and the Approver continues cyclically until the feature is approved.
Once the feature is approved the feature branch is merged.
When the feature branch is merged the dynamic hosting environment and all components are retrograded.
